The following is a List of Station Coordinates of the CWB Free-Field 
Accelerographs based on the TWD97 geodetic coordinate system.  These 
station coordinates were adopted for use by the Central Weather Bureau 
of Taiwan (CWB) on February 4, 2008.  However, a very few stations are
given in the TWD67 geodetic coordinate system as noted below.


NOTE:

Stcode = 6-charcter station name for the accelerograph network, 
         or 3- or 4-character name for a station of the regular  
         seismic network. There are two seismic networks Operated 
         by CWB: the regular stations and free-field Accelerograph 
         stations.  Most regular stations have Accelerograph stations 
         operated at the same site.
Model = Accelerograph model.
SN1   = 4-character Accelerograph Serial Number. 

Latitude = North latitude in degrees.
Longitude = East longitude in degrees.
Elv. = Elevation in meters.
Rk = "+" on TWD97 geodetic coordinate system; "-" on TWD67 coordinate system.

Full Scale = full scale (+ and -) of the accelerograph (in g).
SN2   = 3-character Accelerograph Serial Number. 
Start Date = Start date of the station in year, month, and day.
End Date = End date of the station (in year, month, and day), if applicable.
